    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-cpb-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped to level 1 per MRL 2 requirements. Discretization error (2.3%) and output comparison (max 14.7% deviation) both within acceptance criteria. The hemolysis prediction methodology is supported by published literature including the systematic review of computational hemolysis models (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) which benchmarks the Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulation against in vitro data across 12 pump geometries, confirming applicability to centrifugal CPB devices at the operating conditions covered by this COU. Model credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for Class II CPB device tolerance assessment.",
